Andrea aka Rayna</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2>Crow</FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Unregistered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>12/24/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>5:45:19 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=406.topic&index=4><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Ahhh..the x-mas season!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Hahaha, well..guess I got lucky this year. I didn't get a tree, cancelled my x-mas trip to Tampa, dropped a few gifts at the ex-wife's house for her and the kids but don't expect any thank-you's or return gifts, turned down 2 offers for going to friends on x-mas eve, turned down 3 offers of x-mas dinner on the 25th, Kim and her Mom are spending the holidays in California with family ....... so ....... I'm all alone and actually looking forward to the peace and quiet! No cookies, no carols, no lights, no tree, no paper to pick-up. Sounds kind of sad but I think every once in awhile it's nice to actually not do anything special. Makes you appreciate it that much more. I remember all the years I spent in the Air Force over seas. So many of my friends had no family so they didn't get any gifts or treats. Christmas eve would be spent playing cards and having a few beers trying to pretend that the lack of family and friends, a tree and gifts really didn't matter. So, tomorrow night, Christmas eve, I'll be cracking open a cold one and sitting out on the balconey and looking at the stars as I raise my beer in a silent toast to all those alone this Christmas season ... wheather by choice or circumstance. My heart is with all of you and your families this season, but my heart goes out to all those alone. Merry Christmas from Texas!!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/bforgottentruthforeignlegion.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dia>Dia</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>12/24/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>1:10:21 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=406.topic&index=5><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Merry Christmas!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Joyeux Noël!</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#6B8E23><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>12/25/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>3:22:55 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=406.topic&index=6><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Merry Christmas!</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">We do our family thing on Christmas eve, so